The Wigan Warriors defeated the
Leeds Rhinos 28-18 in the final of the rugby league Challenge
Cup.  Jeff Lima touched down twice as Wigan outscored Leeds five
tries to four at Wembley Stadium in  London . Josh Charnley, Joel
Tomkins and Thomas Leuluai also had tries as the Warriors won
the knockout competition for a record-extending 18th time.  Ryan Hall touched down twice for Leeds, which lost last
yearâ€™s final to Warrington. Jamie Jones-Buchanan and Carl Ablett
also scored tries for the Rhinos.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
